This paper investigates the performance variations within IaaS services, which falls under the category of cloud computing (cs.CC) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The study also involves longitudinal observations and data analysis, which could be categorized under networked and internet-based systems (cs.NI) and software engineering (cs.SE). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for automated decision-making processes, which could be related to computer security and cryptography (cs.CR).
